bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The collection is focused on the history of the greater Washington, D.C. metropolitan area. More specifically it documents the history of DC communities, focusing on community structure, organizations, politics, events, transportation and difficulties, such as crime. Upon receipt the collection was already divided into labeled folders. In processing this collection I abided by this organization and merely sorted these folders into the broader series of: Geographic Locations, Organizations, Politics and Individuals.
The collection is housed in 15 boxes and consists mostly of newspaper articles, brochures, pamphlets and letters. The dates of the documents range from the late 1800s until the late 1990s.
The donation was made in January 1995, by Howard Gillette.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The collection includes materials on the history of the greater Washington, D.C. metropolitan area. The collection documents the history of DC communities, focusing on community structure, organizations, politics, events, transportation and difficulties, such as crime and includes paper articles, brochures, pamphlets and letters.

The collection was received already divided into labeled folders, therefore the organization remains according to provenance, but has been divided into the following four series: Geographic Locations; Organizations; Politics; and Individual.
The collection is housed in 15 boxes and ranges in date from the late 1800s until the late 1990s.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: Geographic locations, Organizations, Politics, and Individual.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes geopraphic locations of the greater Washington area from 1873-1995.
